isch hervorragend aufbereitete Abbildungen und viele aktuelle Fotos. Über 800 Übungsaufgaben verschiedener Schwierigkeitsgrade, die zu einem großen Teil mit vollständigen Lösungen vorliegen, ermöglichen dem Studierenden, sein Wissen selbständig zu überprüfen.  aReaders appreciate this textbook primarily for its balanced didactic approach. It explains the mathematics of wave motion in an easy-to-understand manner and covers in detail both classical and modern methods of optics. The author's goal here is to unify the optics within the framework of a few overarching concepts so that students have a self-contained, cohesive picture.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBeugung. 4aElektromagnetismus. 4aFourier-Optik. 4aGeometrische Optik. 4aInterferenz. 4aPolarisation. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Electromagnetism.2bisacsh  a.  aDiffraction.  aElectromagnetism.  aFourier optics.  aGeometrical optics.  aInterference.  aPolarization.1 aLippert, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPearson Education Inc., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023z9783111318660oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831110258410 cprintz978311102525440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311102559940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111025599423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111025599/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alle